e the 220 count. What Ed Balls was subjected to during his days at home I can only imagine in a bad dystopian dream. Does he really think that by any objective criteria we live in a society that is so thoroughly dangerous for kids? I have just taken my daughter to two kids' parties where there were treasure hunts, tree-climbing, swordfights, karaoke, parents drinking ALCOHOL... The minority of people who voted for Balls and his government will no doubt support him. "/><type4:DocumentMetaData xmi:id="13" sofa="1" begin="0" end="777" language="en" documentId="1042" isLastSegment="false"/><types:WebArgumentMetadata xmi:id="24" sofa="1" begin="0" end="0" author="FoundThePlot" date="07 November 2009 7:05pm" docType="artcomment" origUrl="http://discussion.theguardian.com/comment-permalink/6756846" topic="homeschooling" thumbsUp="2" thumbsDown="0" origId="1042" notes="" title="Ridiculous rules for home schools"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="39" sofa="1" begin="0" end="777"/><cas:View sofa="1" members="13 24 39"/></xmi:XMI>